{
  "texts": [
    "Participants were compensated at a rate of £9/hr for completing the surveys and were awarded a £3 bonus at the end of the study if they completed all 6 weekly surveys.",
    "Critically, participants were not financially compensated for their engagement with either the Limbic app or PDF workbook.",
    "They were encouraged to engage with their assigned materials 4 times per week but were clearly instructed that their engagement would not affect their payment.",
    "Our primary outcome measures included: 1) engagement with the therapeutic materials, and 2) change in anxiety and depression symptom severity.",
    "We operationalised engagement as the total time spent in the Limbic app or viewing the PDF, as well as the total number of times the app or PDF website was opened."
  ]
}